    • loadStableType

      public Type loadStableType​(String typeName) throws IOException
      Loads a type by name. As it is resolved by the server, the name can be a qualified, unqualified or alias name; anything acceptable to the server. Stable types are those that are expected to be available and not to change; an example being "hstore". This method caches the type in the non-shared registry. Any changes to the type (e.g. dropping and re-creating the "hstore" extension) will cause the cache to become stale.
      Parameters:
      typeName - Name of the type (can be anything accepted by the server)
      Returns:
      Type object or null, if none found
      Throws:
      IOException
